          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "smolagents and Pydantic AI: Two Minimal Frameworks"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "The agent framework ecosystem includes two deliberately minimal libraries that take opposing design philosophies: "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "smolagents",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "bold"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " (from Hugging Face) and "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Pydantic AI",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "bold"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " (from the Pydantic team). Both reject the complexity of LangChain or CrewAI in favor of clean APIs that map directly onto the LLM's actual capabilities."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "smolagents' central idea is that agents should "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "generate and execute Python code",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "bold"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": ", not JSON tool calls. Instead of the LLM producing "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "{\"tool\": \"calculate\", \"args\": {\"x\": 2}}",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": ", it writes "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "result = calculate(x=2)",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " and the framework executes it. This lets the model compose tools, do arithmetic, use loops \u2014 all in code."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Pydantic AI's central idea is "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "type safety and dependency injection",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "bold"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": ". Agent inputs, tool arguments, and agent outputs are all Pydantic-validated. Tools receive a "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "RunContext",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " carrying typed dependencies (database connections, API clients, user context) injected at runtime \u2014 the same pattern as FastAPI's dependency injection."
          }
        ]
      },
